{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The question today is not:"},{"time":3000,"text":"Why did we invade Afghanistan?"},{"time":5000,"text":"The question is:"},{"time":7000,"text":"why are we still in Afghanistan"},{"time":10000,"text":"one decade later?"},{"time":13000,"text":"Why are we spending"},{"time":15000,"text":"$135 billion?"},{"time":19000,"text":"Why have we got 130,000 troops on the ground?"},{"time":23000,"text":"Why were more people killed"},{"time":25000,"text":"last month"},{"time":27000,"text":"than in any preceding month"},{"time":29000,"text":"of this conflict?"},{"time":31000,"text":"How has this happened?"},{"time":33000,"text":"The last 20 years"},{"time":36000,"text":"has been the age of intervention,"},{"time":39000,"text":"and Afghanistan is simply one act"},{"time":42000,"text":"in a five-act tragedy."},{"time":44000,"text":"We came out of the end of the Cold War"},{"time":47000,"text":"in despair."},{"time":49000,"text":"We faced Rwanda;"},{"time":51000,"text":"we faced Bosnia,"},{"time":53000,"text":"and then we rediscovered our confidence."},{"time":56000,"text":"In the third act, we went into Bosnia and Kosovo"},{"time":59000,"text":"and we seemed to succeed."},{"time":62000,"text":"In the fourth act, with our hubris,"},{"time":64000,"text":"our overconfidence developing,"},{"time":66000,"text":"we invaded Iraq and Afghanistan,"},{"time":69000,"text":"and in the fifth act,"},{"time":71000,"text":"we plunged into a humiliating mess."}]},{"cues":[{"time":75000,"text":"So the question is: What are we doing?"},{"time":78000,"text":"Why are we still stuck in Afghanistan?"},{"time":81000,"text":"And the answer, of course,"},{"time":83000,"text":"that we keep being given"},{"time":85000,"text":"is as follows:"},{"time":87000,"text":"we're told that we went into Afghanistan"},{"time":89000,"text":"because of 9/11,"},{"time":91000,"text":"and that we remain there"},{"time":93000,"text":"because the Taliban poses an existential threat"},{"time":95000,"text":"to global security."},{"time":97000,"text":"In the words of President Obama,"},{"time":100000,"text":"\"If the Taliban take over again,"},{"time":102000,"text":"they will invite back Al-Qaeda,"},{"time":104000,"text":"who will try to kill as many of our people"},{"time":107000,"text":"as they possibly can.\""},{"time":110000,"text":"The story that we're told"},{"time":112000,"text":"is that there was a \"light footprint\" initially --"},{"time":114000,"text":"in other words, that we ended up in a situation"},{"time":116000,"text":"where we didn't have enough troops,"},{"time":118000,"text":"we didn't have enough resources,"},{"time":120000,"text":"that Afghans were frustrated --"},{"time":122000,"text":"they felt there wasn't enough progress"},{"time":124000,"text":"and economic development and security,"},{"time":127000,"text":"and therefore the Taliban came back --"},{"time":129000,"text":"that we responded in 2005 and 2006"},{"time":132000,"text":"with troop deployments,"},{"time":134000,"text":"but we still didn't put enough troops on the ground."},{"time":138000,"text":"And that it wasn't until 2009,"},{"time":141000,"text":"when President Obama signed off on a surge,"},{"time":144000,"text":"that we finally had,"},{"time":146000,"text":"in the words of Secretary Clinton,"},{"time":148000,"text":"\"the strategy, the leadership and the resources.\""},{"time":151000,"text":"So, as the president now reassures us,"},{"time":154000,"text":"we are on track to achieve our goals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":159000,"text":"All of this is wrong."},{"time":162000,"text":"Every one of those statements is wrong."},{"time":166000,"text":"Afghanistan does not"},{"time":168000,"text":"pose an existential threat"},{"time":170000,"text":"to global security."},{"time":172000,"text":"It is extremely unlikely"},{"time":174000,"text":"the Taliban would ever be able to take over the country --"},{"time":177000,"text":"extremely unlikely they'd be able to seize Kabul."},{"time":179000,"text":"They simply don't have a conventional military option."},{"time":182000,"text":"And even if they were able to do so, even if I'm wrong,"},{"time":185000,"text":"it's extremely unlikely"},{"time":187000,"text":"the Taliban would invite back Al-Qaeda."},{"time":189000,"text":"From the Taliban's point of view,"},{"time":191000,"text":"that was their number one mistake last time."},{"time":194000,"text":"If they hadn't invited back Al-Qaeda,"},{"time":196000,"text":"they would still be in power today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"And even if I'm wrong about those two things,"},{"time":201000,"text":"even if they were able to take back the country,"},{"time":203000,"text":"even if they were to invite back Al-Qaeda,"},{"time":206000,"text":"it's extremely unlikely"},{"time":208000,"text":"that Al-Qaeda would significantly enhance"},{"time":210000,"text":"its ability to harm the United States"},{"time":212000,"text":"or harm Europe."},{"time":215000,"text":"Because this isn't the 1990s anymore."},{"time":217000,"text":"If the Al-Qaeda base"},{"time":219000,"text":"was to be established near Ghazni,"},{"time":221000,"text":"we would hit them very hard,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and it would be very, very difficult"},{"time":225000,"text":"for the Taliban to protect them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227000,"text":"Furthermore, it's simply not true"},{"time":230000,"text":"that what went wrong in Afghanistan"},{"time":232000,"text":"is the light footprint."},{"time":234000,"text":"In my experience, in fact,"},{"time":236000,"text":"the light footprint was extremely helpful."},{"time":240000,"text":"And these troops that we brought in --"},{"time":243000,"text":"it's a great picture of David Beckham"},{"time":245000,"text":"there on the sub-machine gun --"},{"time":247000,"text":"made the situation worse, not better."},{"time":250000,"text":"When I walked across Afghanistan"},{"time":252000,"text":"in the winter of 2001-2002,"},{"time":255000,"text":"what I saw was scenes like this."},{"time":257000,"text":"A girl, if you're lucky,"},{"time":259000,"text":"in the corner of a dark room --"},{"time":261000,"text":"lucky to be able to look at the Koran."},{"time":264000,"text":"But in those early days"},{"time":266000,"text":"when we're told we didn't have enough troops and enough resources,"},{"time":268000,"text":"we made a lot of progress in Afghanistan."},{"time":270000,"text":"Within a few months,"},{"time":272000,"text":"there were two and a half million more girls in school."},{"time":275000,"text":"In Sangin where I was sick in 2002,"},{"time":278000,"text":"the nearest health clinic"},{"time":280000,"text":"was within three days walk."},{"time":282000,"text":"Today, there are 14 health clinics"},{"time":285000,"text":"in that area alone."},{"time":287000,"text":"There was amazing improvements."},{"time":289000,"text":"We went from almost no Afghans"},{"time":291000,"text":"having mobile telephones during the Taliban"},{"time":293000,"text":"to a situation where, almost overnight,"},{"time":295000,"text":"three million Afghans had mobile telephones."},{"time":299000,"text":"And we had progress in the free media."},{"time":301000,"text":"We had progress in elections --"},{"time":303000,"text":"all of this with the so-called light footprint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"But when we began to bring more money,"},{"time":309000,"text":"when we began to invest more resources,"},{"time":312000,"text":"things got worse, not better. How?"},{"time":315000,"text":"Well first see, if you put 125 billion dollars a year"},{"time":318000,"text":"into a country like Afghanistan"},{"time":320000,"text":"where the entire revenue of the Afghan state"},{"time":323000,"text":"is one billion dollars a year,"},{"time":325000,"text":"you drown everything."},{"time":328000,"text":"It's not simply corruption and waste"},{"time":330000,"text":"that you create;"},{"time":332000,"text":"you essentially replace the priorities of the Afghan government,"},{"time":335000,"text":"the elected Afghan government,"},{"time":337000,"text":"with the micromanaging tendencies"},{"time":339000,"text":"of foreigners on short tours"},{"time":342000,"text":"with their own priorities."},{"time":344000,"text":"And the same is true for the troops."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346000,"text":"When I walked across Afghanistan,"},{"time":348000,"text":"I stayed with people like this."},{"time":350000,"text":"This is Commandant Haji Malem Mohsin Khan of Kamenj."},{"time":353000,"text":"Commandant Haji Malem Mohsin Khan of Kamenj was a great host."},{"time":356000,"text":"He was very generous,"},{"time":358000,"text":"like many of the Afghans I stayed with."},{"time":360000,"text":"But he was also considerably more conservative,"},{"time":363000,"text":"considerably more anti-foreign,"},{"time":365000,"text":"considerably more Islamist"},{"time":367000,"text":"than we'd like to acknowledge."},{"time":370000,"text":"This man, for example, Mullah Mustafa,"},{"time":372000,"text":"tried to shoot me."},{"time":374000,"text":"And the reason I'm looking a little bit perplexed in this photograph"},{"time":377000,"text":"is I was somewhat frightened,"},{"time":379000,"text":"and I was too afraid on this occasion"},{"time":381000,"text":"to ask him, having run for an hour through the desert"},{"time":383000,"text":"and taken refuge in this house,"},{"time":385000,"text":"why he had turned up and wanted to have his photograph taken with me."},{"time":389000,"text":"But 18 months later, I asked him"},{"time":391000,"text":"why he had tried to shoot me."},{"time":393000,"text":"And Mullah Mustafa -- he's the man with the pen and paper --"},{"time":395000,"text":"explained that the man sitting immediately to the left as you look at the photograph,"},{"time":398000,"text":"Nadir Shah"},{"time":400000,"text":"had bet him that he couldn't hit me."},{"time":403000,"text":"Now this is not to say"},{"time":405000,"text":"Afghanistan is a place full of people like Mullah Mustafa."},{"time":408000,"text":"It's not; it's a wonderful place"},{"time":411000,"text":"full of incredible energy and intelligence."},{"time":414000,"text":"But it is a place"},{"time":416000,"text":"where the putting-in of the troops"},{"time":418000,"text":"has increased the violence rather than decreased it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421000,"text":"2005, Anthony Fitzherbert,"},{"time":423000,"text":"an agricultural engineer,"},{"time":425000,"text":"could travel through Helmand,"},{"time":427000,"text":"could stay in Nad Ali, Sangin and Ghoresh,"},{"time":429000,"text":"which are now the names of villages where fighting is taking place."},{"time":432000,"text":"Today, he could never do that."},{"time":435000,"text":"So the idea that we deployed the troops"},{"time":437000,"text":"to respond to the Taliban insurgency"},{"time":439000,"text":"is mistaken."},{"time":441000,"text":"Rather than preceding the insurgency,"},{"time":443000,"text":"the Taliban followed the troop deployment,"},{"time":446000,"text":"and as far as I'm concerned,"},{"time":448000,"text":"the troop deployment caused their return."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451000,"text":"Now is this a new idea?"},{"time":453000,"text":"No, there have been any number of people"},{"time":455000,"text":"saying this over the last seven years."},{"time":458000,"text":"I ran a center at Harvard"},{"time":460000,"text":"from 2008 to 2010,"},{"time":462000,"text":"and there were people like Michael Semple there"},{"time":464000,"text":"who speak Afghan languages fluently,"},{"time":466000,"text":"who've traveled to almost every district in the country."},{"time":469000,"text":"Andrew Wilder, for example,"},{"time":472000,"text":"born on the Pakistan-Iranian border,"},{"time":475000,"text":"served his whole life"},{"time":477000,"text":"in Pakistan and Afghanistan."},{"time":479000,"text":"Paul Fishstein who began working there in 1978 --"},{"time":481000,"text":"worked for Save the Children,"},{"time":483000,"text":"ran the Afghan research and evaluation unit."},{"time":487000,"text":"These are people"},{"time":489000,"text":"who were able to say consistently"},{"time":491000,"text":"that the increase in development aid"},{"time":493000,"text":"was making Afghanistan less secure, not more secure --"},{"time":496000,"text":"that the counter-insurgency strategy"},{"time":498000,"text":"was not working and would not work."},{"time":501000,"text":"And yet, nobody listened to them."},{"time":504000,"text":"Instead,"},{"time":506000,"text":"there was a litany of astonishing optimism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"Beginning in 2004,"},{"time":511000,"text":"every general came in saying,"},{"time":514000,"text":"\"I've inherited a dismal situation,"},{"time":516000,"text":"but finally I have the right resources and the correct strategy,"},{"time":519000,"text":"which will deliver,\""},{"time":521000,"text":"in General Barno's word in 2004,"},{"time":523000,"text":"the \"decisive year.\""},{"time":525000,"text":"Well guess what? It didn't."},{"time":527000,"text":"But it wasn't sufficient to prevent General Abuzaid saying"},{"time":530000,"text":"that he had the strategy and the resources"},{"time":532000,"text":"to deliver, in 2005,"},{"time":534000,"text":"the \"decisive year.\""},{"time":536000,"text":"Or General David Richards to come in 2006"},{"time":539000,"text":"and say he had the strategy and the resources"},{"time":541000,"text":"to deliver the \"crunch year.\""},{"time":543000,"text":"Or in 2007,"},{"time":545000,"text":"the Norwegian deputy foreign minister, Espen Eide,"},{"time":548000,"text":"to say that that would deliver the \"decisive year.\""},{"time":551000,"text":"Or in 2008, Major General Champoux"},{"time":553000,"text":"to come in and say he would deliver the \"decisive year.\""},{"time":556000,"text":"Or in 2009, my great friend,"},{"time":558000,"text":"General Stanley McChrystal,"},{"time":560000,"text":"who said that he was \"knee-deep in the decisive year.\""},{"time":563000,"text":"Or in 2010,"},{"time":565000,"text":"the U.K. foreign secretary, David Miliband,"},{"time":568000,"text":"who said that at last we would deliver the \"decisive year.\""},{"time":571000,"text":"And you'll be delighted to hear in 2011, today,"},{"time":574000,"text":"that Guido Westerwelle, the German foreign minister,"},{"time":577000,"text":"assures us that we are in the \"decisive year.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":582000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":588000,"text":"How do we allow"},{"time":590000,"text":"any of this to happen?"},{"time":592000,"text":"Well the answer, of course, is,"},{"time":594000,"text":"if you spend 125 billion or 130 billion"},{"time":596000,"text":"dollars a year in a country,"},{"time":599000,"text":"you co-opt almost everybody."},{"time":601000,"text":"Even the aid agencies,"},{"time":603000,"text":"who begin to receive an enormous amount of money"},{"time":605000,"text":"from the U.S. and the European governments"},{"time":607000,"text":"to build schools and clinics,"},{"time":609000,"text":"are somewhat disinclined"},{"time":611000,"text":"to challenge the idea"},{"time":613000,"text":"that Afghanistan is an existential threat"},{"time":615000,"text":"to global security."},{"time":617000,"text":"They're worried, in other words,"},{"time":619000,"text":"that if anybody believes that it wasn't such a threat --"},{"time":621000,"text":"Oxfam, Save the Children"},{"time":623000,"text":"wouldn't get the money"},{"time":625000,"text":"to build their hospitals and schools."},{"time":627000,"text":"It's also very difficult to confront a general"},{"time":629000,"text":"with medals on his chest."},{"time":631000,"text":"It's very difficult for a politician,"},{"time":634000,"text":"because you're afraid that many lives have been lost in vain."},{"time":637000,"text":"You feel deep, deep guilt."},{"time":639000,"text":"You exaggerate your fears,"},{"time":642000,"text":"and you're terrified about the humiliation"},{"time":645000,"text":"of defeat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647000,"text":"What is the solution to this?"},{"time":649000,"text":"Well the solution to this"},{"time":651000,"text":"is we need to find a way"},{"time":653000,"text":"that people like Michael Semple, or those other people,"},{"time":656000,"text":"who are telling the truth, who know the country,"},{"time":659000,"text":"who've spent 30 years on the ground --"},{"time":661000,"text":"and most importantly of all,"},{"time":663000,"text":"the missing component of this --"},{"time":665000,"text":"Afghans themselves,"},{"time":667000,"text":"who understand what is going on."},{"time":670000,"text":"We need to somehow get their message"},{"time":673000,"text":"to the policymakers."},{"time":675000,"text":"And this is very difficult to do"},{"time":677000,"text":"because of our structures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":679000,"text":"The first thing we need to change"},{"time":681000,"text":"is the structures of our government."},{"time":683000,"text":"Very, very sadly,"},{"time":685000,"text":"our foreign services, the United Nations,"},{"time":687000,"text":"the military in these countries"},{"time":689000,"text":"have very little idea of what's going on."},{"time":691000,"text":"The average British soldier is on a tour of only six months;"},{"time":694000,"text":"Italian soldiers, on tours of four months;"},{"time":697000,"text":"the American military, on tours of 12 months."},{"time":700000,"text":"Diplomats are locked in embassy compounds."},{"time":703000,"text":"When they go out, they travel in these curious armored vehicles"},{"time":706000,"text":"with these somewhat threatening security teams"},{"time":709000,"text":"who ready 24 hours in advance"},{"time":711000,"text":"who say you can only stay on the ground for an hour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":713000,"text":"In the British embassy in Afghanistan"},{"time":715000,"text":"in 2008,"},{"time":717000,"text":"an embassy of 350 people,"},{"time":719000,"text":"there were only three people who could speak Dari,"},{"time":722000,"text":"the main language of Afghanistan, at a decent level."},{"time":725000,"text":"And there was not a single Pashto speaker."},{"time":728000,"text":"In the Afghan section in London"},{"time":731000,"text":"responsible for governing Afghan policy on the ground,"},{"time":734000,"text":"I was told last year"},{"time":736000,"text":"that there was not a single staff member"},{"time":738000,"text":"of the foreign office in that section"},{"time":741000,"text":"who had ever served"},{"time":743000,"text":"on a posting in Afghanistan."},{"time":745000,"text":"So we need to change that institutional culture."},{"time":747000,"text":"And I could make the same points about the United States"},{"time":750000,"text":"and the United Nations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"Secondly, we need to aim off of the optimism of the generals."},{"time":755000,"text":"We need to make sure that we're a little bit suspicious,"},{"time":758000,"text":"that we understand that optimism"},{"time":760000,"text":"is in the DNA of the military,"},{"time":762000,"text":"that we don't respond to it"},{"time":764000,"text":"with quite as much alacrity."},{"time":766000,"text":"And thirdly, we need to have some humility."},{"time":769000,"text":"We need to begin from the position"},{"time":771000,"text":"that our knowledge, our power,"},{"time":773000,"text":"our legitimacy"},{"time":775000,"text":"is limited."},{"time":777000,"text":"This doesn't mean"},{"time":779000,"text":"that intervention around the world is a disaster."},{"time":781000,"text":"It isn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"Bosnia and Kosovo"},{"time":785000,"text":"were signal successes,"},{"time":787000,"text":"great successes."},{"time":790000,"text":"Today when you go to Bosnia"},{"time":792000,"text":"it is almost impossible to believe"},{"time":794000,"text":"that what we saw in the early 1990s happened."},{"time":798000,"text":"It's almost impossible to believe the progress we've made"},{"time":801000,"text":"since 1994."},{"time":804000,"text":"Refugee return,"},{"time":806000,"text":"which the United Nations High Commission for Refugees"},{"time":808000,"text":"thought would be extremely unlikely,"},{"time":810000,"text":"has largely happened."},{"time":812000,"text":"A million properties have been returned."},{"time":814000,"text":"Borders between the Bosniak territory"},{"time":816000,"text":"and the Bosnian-Serb territory have calmed down."},{"time":819000,"text":"The national army has shrunk."},{"time":822000,"text":"The crime rates in Bosnia today"},{"time":824000,"text":"are lower than they are in Sweden."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"This has been done"},{"time":830000,"text":"by an incredible, principled effort"},{"time":833000,"text":"by the international community,"},{"time":835000,"text":"and, of course, above all,"},{"time":837000,"text":"by Bosnians themselves."},{"time":839000,"text":"But you need to look at context."},{"time":841000,"text":"And this is what we've lost in Afghanistan and Iraq."},{"time":844000,"text":"You need to understand that in those places"},{"time":846000,"text":"what really mattered"},{"time":848000,"text":"was, firstly, the role of Tudman and Milosevic"},{"time":850000,"text":"in coming to the agreement,"},{"time":852000,"text":"and then the fact those men went,"},{"time":855000,"text":"that the regional situation improved,"},{"time":857000,"text":"that the European Union could offer Bosnia"},{"time":860000,"text":"something extraordinary:"},{"time":862000,"text":"the chance to be part"},{"time":864000,"text":"of a new thing, a new club,"},{"time":866000,"text":"a chance to join something bigger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":869000,"text":"And finally, we need to understand that in Bosnia and Kosovo,"},{"time":872000,"text":"a lot of the secret of what we did,"},{"time":874000,"text":"a lot of the secret of our success,"},{"time":876000,"text":"was our humility --"},{"time":878000,"text":"was the tentative nature of our engagement."},{"time":881000,"text":"We criticized people a lot in Bosnia"},{"time":883000,"text":"for being quite slow to take on war criminals."},{"time":885000,"text":"We criticized them"},{"time":887000,"text":"for being quite slow to return refugees."},{"time":889000,"text":"But that slowness, that caution,"},{"time":891000,"text":"the fact that President Clinton initially said"},{"time":894000,"text":"that American troops would only be deployed for a year,"},{"time":896000,"text":"turned out to be a strength,"},{"time":898000,"text":"and it helped us to put our priorities right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"One of the saddest things"},{"time":903000,"text":"about our involvement in Afghanistan"},{"time":905000,"text":"is that we've got our priorities out of sync."},{"time":907000,"text":"We're not matching our resources to our priorities."},{"time":910000,"text":"Because if what we're interested in is terrorism,"},{"time":913000,"text":"Pakistan is far more important than Afghanistan."},{"time":916000,"text":"If what we're interested in is regional stability,"},{"time":918000,"text":"Egypt is far more important."},{"time":920000,"text":"If what we're worried about is poverty and development,"},{"time":923000,"text":"sub-Saharan Africa is far more important."},{"time":926000,"text":"This doesn't mean that Afghanistan doesn't matter,"},{"time":929000,"text":"but that it's one of 40 countries in the world"},{"time":931000,"text":"with which we need to engage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":933000,"text":"So if I can finish with a metaphor for intervention,"},{"time":937000,"text":"what we need to think of"},{"time":940000,"text":"is something like mountain rescue."},{"time":943000,"text":"Why mountain rescue?"},{"time":945000,"text":"Because when people talk about intervention,"},{"time":948000,"text":"they imagine that some scientific theory --"},{"time":950000,"text":"the Rand Corporation goes around"},{"time":952000,"text":"counting 43 previous insurgencies"},{"time":955000,"text":"producing mathematical formula"},{"time":957000,"text":"saying you need one trained counter-insurgent"},{"time":959000,"text":"for every 20 members of the population."},{"time":962000,"text":"This is the wrong way of looking at it."},{"time":964000,"text":"You need to look at it in the way that you look at mountain rescue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":967000,"text":"When you're doing mountain rescue,"},{"time":969000,"text":"you don't take a doctorate in mountain rescue,"},{"time":972000,"text":"you look for somebody who knows the terrain."},{"time":975000,"text":"It's about context."},{"time":977000,"text":"You understand that you can prepare,"},{"time":979000,"text":"but the amount of preparation you can do"},{"time":981000,"text":"is limited --"},{"time":983000,"text":"you can take some water, you can have a map,"},{"time":985000,"text":"you can have a pack."},{"time":987000,"text":"But what really matters"},{"time":989000,"text":"is two kinds of problems --"},{"time":991000,"text":"problems that occur on the mountain"},{"time":993000,"text":"which you couldn't anticipate,"},{"time":995000,"text":"such as, for example, ice on a slope,"},{"time":998000,"text":"but which you can get around,"},{"time":1000000,"text":"and problems which you couldn't anticipate"},{"time":1003000,"text":"and which you can't get around,"},{"time":1005000,"text":"like a sudden blizzard or an avalanche"},{"time":1007000,"text":"or a change in the weather."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1009000,"text":"And the key to this"},{"time":1011000,"text":"is a guide who has been on that mountain,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"in every temperature,"},{"time":1016000,"text":"at every period --"},{"time":1018000,"text":"a guide who, above all,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"knows when to turn back,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"who doesn't press on relentlessly"},{"time":1024000,"text":"when conditions turn against them."},{"time":1026000,"text":"What we look for"},{"time":1028000,"text":"in firemen, in climbers, in policemen,"},{"time":1031000,"text":"and what we should look for in intervention,"},{"time":1033000,"text":"is intelligent risk takers --"},{"time":1035000,"text":"not people who plunge blind off a cliff,"},{"time":1038000,"text":"not people who jump into a burning room,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"but who weigh their risks,"},{"time":1043000,"text":"weigh their responsibilities."},{"time":1045000,"text":"Because the worst thing we have done in Afghanistan"},{"time":1048000,"text":"is this idea"},{"time":1050000,"text":"that failure is not an option."},{"time":1053000,"text":"It makes failure invisible,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"inconceivable and inevitable."},{"time":1059000,"text":"And if we can resist"},{"time":1061000,"text":"this crazy slogan,"},{"time":1063000,"text":"we shall discover --"},{"time":1065000,"text":"in Egypt, in Syria, in Libya,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"and anywhere else we go in the world --"},{"time":1070000,"text":"that if we can often do much less than we pretend,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"we can do much more than we fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1077000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you very much."},{"time":1084000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you very much."},{"time":1087000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1091000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099000,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":1101000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you."},{"time":1103000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1105000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107000,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Rory, you mentioned Libya at the end."},{"time":1110000,"text":"Just briefly, what's your take on the current events there"},{"time":1113000,"text":"and the intervention?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115000,"text":"Rory Stewart: Okay, I think Libya poses the classic problem."},{"time":1118000,"text":"The problem in Libya"},{"time":1120000,"text":"is that we are always pushing for the black or white."},{"time":1122000,"text":"We imagine there are only two choices:"},{"time":1124000,"text":"either full engagement and troop deployment"},{"time":1127000,"text":"or total isolation."},{"time":1129000,"text":"And we are always being tempted up to our neck."},{"time":1132000,"text":"We put our toes in and we go up to our neck."},{"time":1134000,"text":"What we should have done in Libya"},{"time":1136000,"text":"is we should have stuck to the U.N. resolution."},{"time":1138000,"text":"We should have limited ourselves very, very strictly"},{"time":1141000,"text":"to the protection of the civilian population in Benghazi."},{"time":1144000,"text":"We could have done that."},{"time":1146000,"text":"We set up a no-fly zone within 48 hours"},{"time":1149000,"text":"because Gaddafi had no planes"},{"time":1151000,"text":"within 48 hours."},{"time":1153000,"text":"Instead of which, we've allowed ourselves to be tempted"},{"time":1156000,"text":"towards regime change."},{"time":1158000,"text":"In doing so, we've destroyed our credibility with the Security Council,"},{"time":1162000,"text":"which means it's very difficult"},{"time":1164000,"text":"to get a resolution on Syria,"},{"time":1166000,"text":"and we're setting ourselves up again for failure."},{"time":1169000,"text":"Once more, humility,"},{"time":1171000,"text":"limits, honesty,"},{"time":1173000,"text":"realistic expectations"},{"time":1175000,"text":"and we could have achieved something to be proud of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1177000,"text":"BG: Rory, thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1179000,"text":"RS: Thank you. (BG: Thank you.)"}]}]}